      "note": "The term ruh (lit., \"spirit\" or \"soul\") has in the Qur'an often the meaning of \"divine inspiration\" (see surah 16, note 2). In the present context, it evidently denotes the contents of the divine inspiration bestowed on the Prophet Muhammad, i.e., the Qur'an (Tabari, Zamakhshari, Razi, Ibn Kathir), which is meant to lead man to a more intensive spiritual life: hence my above rendering."
